Here is the cleaned up text:

Post CRM Analytics Dashboards and Lenses to Slack

Facilitate data-driven collaboration by sharing directly from CRM Analytics to your channels in Slack. Slack recipients get a snapshot showing the latest data. Or post a link with quick action buttons.

REQUIRED EDITIONS AND USER PERMISSIONS
Available in: Lightning Experience and Salesforce Classic
Available in: Professional, Enterprise, Unlimited, and Developer Editions

PERMISSIONS NEEDED
To use CRM Analytics for Slack: Connect Salesforce with Slack
To download data from widgets and lenses using the CRM Analytics user interface: Download CRM Analytics Data
To share images of dashboards and widgets when Secure Image Sharing and Downloading is enabled: Share CRM Analytics Images

Enable Dashboard Views must be on to view snapshots. The setting is enabled by default.

To set up the Post to Slack feature, complete these steps:

From Setup, in the Quick Find box, enter Slack, and then select Slack Apps Setup.
At step 2, click Accept to agree to the Terms and Conditions.
In the left navigation panel, select CRM Analytics for Slack and click Agree and enable Slack integration.

Each user must then add CRM Analytics for Slack to their personal Slack sidebar and connect their Salesforce account.

After setting up the feature, the Post to Slack icon appears on dashboards and lenses. Click the icon to select the Slack workspace and channels where you want to share the item. You can add up to 20 channels per post. Optionally, add a comment to spark conversation with your teammates.

You can post with or without a snapshot. Both options include a link to the item in CRM Analytics.

Posts without a snapshot have buttons for the following actions: view snapshot, view details, subscribe (for dashboards only), and download as an accessible .pdf file. The accessible .pdf file includes an image plus the dashboard or lens data in screen-reader friendly, tabular format.

NOTE The snapshot is an image of your personal view, including any confidential data. Consider that after you share it others can see and share your personal view. Alternatively, sharing without an image lets others run their own snapshot with their default views and security predicates.

SEE ALSO
CRM Analytics for Slack
title: Share Dashboards to Slack
